BT 1 0 0 1 0 65.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 15 TL .929808 Tw (The first question most Godot developers ask is: why not call the AI API directly from GDScript? The answer is) Tj T* 0 Tw .666462 Tw (authentication security, flexibility, and capability. GDScript has no way to safely store API keys \227 any HTTP call) Tj T* 0 Tw .081879 Tw (from Godot ships your key in plain text inside the binary. A local Python server keeps keys in a .env file, adds retry) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.352556 Tw (logic, manages multiple providers, handles streaming, and can run VLM screenshot analysis \227 none of which) Tj T* 0 Tw (GDScript can do alone. The server runs on localhost:8000. Your game never talks to OpenAI or Google directly.) Tj T* ET
