BT 1 0 0 1 0 142 Tm /F3 7.5 Tf 11.5 TL (from provider_gemini import gemini_complete import pathlib AUDIT_PROMPT = """ You are an accessibility) Tj T* (auditor for video games. Analyse this UI screenshot and check for: 1. COLOUR CONTRAST: Do text and) Tj T* (backgrounds meet WCAG 2.1 AA \(4.5:1 ratio\)? 2. TEXT SIZE: Is any text smaller than 16px equivalent? 3.) Tj T* (COLOUR ONLY INFO: Is any critical info conveyed only by colour \(no shape/text\)? 4. COLOUR BLINDNESS:) Tj T* (Would this UI be unreadable for deuteranopia \(red/green\)? 5. MOTION: Any flashing elements that could) Tj T* (trigger photosensitive epilepsy? 6. BUTTON SIZE: Are interactive elements at least 44x44px equivalent?) Tj T* (Return JSON: { "issues": [{"type": str, "severity": "critical|major|minor", "description": str}],) Tj T* ("passed": ["list of checks that passed"], "accessibility_score": int 0-100 } """ async def) Tj T* (audit_screenshot\(screenshot_path: str\) -> dict: import json result = await gemini_complete\(AUDIT_PROMPT,) Tj T* (thinking="medium", image_path=screenshot_path\) raw = result["text"] s, e = raw.find\("{"\),) Tj T* (raw.rfind\("}"\)+1 if s == -1: return {"error": "No JSON in response"} return json.loads\(raw[s:e]\) # Run on) Tj T* (every screen in your game before each release. # Cost: $0.006 per screenshot. A 50-screen audit costs) Tj T* ($0.30. # Catches issues that would otherwise require a professional accessibility audit.) Tj T* ET
